<h2>Aside 1.5.7</h2>

<p class="intro">Tooltips, round two: quieter and consistent.</p>

<h3>Changed</h3>
<ul>
  <li><b>One tooltip system.</b> Every tooltip now uses the same style. Action buttons show theirs immediately; explanatory hints (like the transcript's "Play from&hellip;" or the tag field) wait a moment, the way macOS tooltips do &mdash; but without the sluggish native delay.</li>
  <li><b>Fewer tooltips.</b> The &times; on the notch pill and the Record button in the Aside window no longer show one.</li>
  <li><b>The Agents chip is just an indicator now.</b> While an agent reads your live transcript, the chip shows it &mdash; clicking it no longer switches agent access off. That control lives in Settings, where an accidental click can't reach it.</li>
</ul>
